The paper deals with pedestrian detection using deep convolutional neural networks, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of boosted decision models, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of pixel labeling and optical flow, which are related to robotics (cs.RO) and multimedia (cs.MM).
